The Trial has started. Katya drops, evading the punches with her small 
size. She counters with two glancing punches and a kick aimed at his 
head.

Ragnar, near Rodimus, sees that he is uneasy about this.

Ragnar: Do not worry, Rodimus. You have to understand that we Clan 
warriors are very proud. We will never follow someone who has not 
proven himself, for this could demonstrate weakness. A weak warrior is 
not a good leader. (He turns to look at Rodimus) But this Owlhawk... 
he is strong. He does lack a bit of self-control, but stepped in the 
ways of the Clans, he would be a deadly one. Katya knows she is likely 
to lose, but this is more a formality. We will follow the Maximals.

--- In nbwrpg@y..., RoboRick007 <rfa007@c...> wrote:
> ::Rodimus Prime/Owlhawk::
> 
> Rodimus really didn't like this idea, but would go with it.
> 
> "I dont think we really have to join or follow each other. Working 
as allies would be fine. However if you must do this, verywell. Go on 
Owlhawk."
> 
> Owlhawk steps out a bit with Katya. He puts his fists up and starts 
to move around a bit. A normal Maximal would probably wait for Katya 
to throw the first punch, but Owlhawk is a little bit different.
> 
> Owlhawk sends two jabs at Katya's face.
